      "purposeInStoryline": "This is the opening lesson of the sub-strand. Its sole purpose is to create a productive intellectual disturbance: learners encounter undeniable physical evidence (the cracked bottle, the protruding ice plug, the crack-line pattern) that contradicts their intuitive expectation that things shrink when cooled. By surfacing and recording their initial mental models before any instruction occurs, the teacher establishes a baseline that every subsequent lesson will refine. The Driving Question Board co-constructed today becomes the living record of the class's growing understanding throughout all lessons in Sub-Strand 1.3.",
      "safetyNotes": "Handle the pre-prepared cracked glass bottle using thick laboratory gloves and place it inside a clear plastic tray to contain any glass fragments. Do not allow learners to handle the cracked bottle directly. If the bottle is shattered, display it sealed inside a transparent zip-lock bag taped to the tray. Remind learners that broken glass is a puncture hazard and must never be touched with bare hands. If a live freezing demonstration is staged for a later lesson, learners must stand at least one metre from the freezer when it is opened."
